               <p>PETER GENTLE. I live in <placeName id="t18310217-262-crimeloc1518">Pitfield-street, Hoxton</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-262-crimeloc1518" type="placeName" value="Pitfield-street, Hoxton"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-262-crimeloc1518" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-262-off1516 t18310217-262-crimeloc1518"></join>, and am an <rs id="t18310217-262-viclabel1519" type="occupation">umbrella-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-262-victim2361 t18310217-262-viclabel1519"></join>. On the 16th of February I was at the back of my shop - I heard a string break, and an iron bar jar; I went to the door, and missed an umbrella - I looked out, and saw the prisoner passing the White Horse, next door; he crossed the road, and I saw the umbrella before him - I ran after him, and as he was turning into Charles-square I asked what he was going to do with my umbrella - he made no answer; the umbrella had been within my door - a person could reach it without coming into the shop; it was fastened by a string, which was tied under the ferrule.</p>
               <p>JURY. Q. Was there a ticket on it? A. Yes, it is on it now.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was passing - I saw it lay five yards from the door, and took it up.</p>
